# secrets.patterns — high-confidence secret regexes (ERE, one per line, # = comment).
# Scanned by hooks/secrets-scan.sh against ADDED lines of the staged git diff.
# DELIBERATELY prefix-anchored / structural: provider-issued keys and private-key
# headers have distinctive shapes, so these almost never false-positive. A generic
# `password = "..."` pattern is intentionally OMITTED — on a BLOCKING §8 hook it
# would misfire on placeholders/empty values far more than it would catch real leaks.
# To extend: add another anchored, low-FP pattern; keep generic-substring greps out.
AKIA[0-9A-Z]{16}
-----BEGIN [A-Z0-9 ]*PRIVATE KEY-----
gh[pousr]_[A-Za-z0-9]{36,}
xox[baprs]-[0-9A-Za-z]{10,}-[0-9A-Za-z]{10,}
AIza[0-9A-Za-z_-]{35}
sk_live_[0-9A-Za-z]{24,}
